          "input_ue_unconnectable": {}
        }
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        " # Higgs Audio v3 - TTS Cloning\n\n  Higgs Audio v3 is a native TTS and zero-shot voice cloning engine with official inline paralinguistic tags.\n\n  - Check the [Higgs inline tag guide](https://github.com/diodiogod/TTS-Audio-Suite/blob/main/docs/HIGGS_AUDIO_V3_INLINE_TAGS.md)\n  - You can also use the Multiline TTS Tag Editor `Inline Tags` tab and select `Higgs Audio v3`\n\n  It behaves like any other TTS engine in the suite:\n  connect the Engine to the unified `TTS Text` or `TTS SRT` nodes and generate.\n\n  Officially, Higgs Audio v3 supports **100+ languages**.\n  The public model card lists **102 languages** total.\n\n  It does **not** support `🔄 Voice Changer`.\n\n  It supports zero-shot cloning with narrator reference audio.\n  A matching reference transcript helps cloning consistency, but Higgs Audio v3 does **not** expose a separate language parameter like Qwen3-TTS.\n  Language is inferred mainly from the input text.\n\n  Higgs Audio v3 supports native inline controls such as:\n\n  - `<|emotion:amusement|>`\n  - `<|style:whispering|>`\n  - `<|prosody:pause|>`\n  - `<|sfx:laughter|>`\n\n  The suite also accepts alias syntax like `<emotion:amusement>` and rewrites it internally to native Higgs format.\n\n  Higgs Audio v3 is not a long-audio dialogue engine like VibeVoice.\n  For long TTS, use the unified chunking controls in the `TTS Text` node.\n\n  If speech cuts too early, raise `max_new_tokens`.\n  For most users, `auto` device, `auto` dtype, and `auto`/`sdpa` attention are the safest defaults."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
